⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Friday
node H1 · H1 · ⟦Friday:H1:1d2156⟧

WHO   — Friday Baldwin, a genetically engineered Artificial Person — stronger, faster, and smarter than the humans who despise her kind — raised without parents and trained as an elite secret courier, forever passing as human in a world that would scorn her if it knew.
WHAT  — The narrator of Friday — a top combat courier moving sealed cargo through the balkanized states of a near-future Earth and its colonies, whose real journey is from self-loathing toward belonging.
WHERE — Across the splintered nations of a future North America, through orbital stations and migration ships, to a colony world where an Artificial Person can finally be simply a person.
WHY   — Because she was built to be discarded yet refused to be less than a person; because she longs for a family and a home in a society that calls her a thing; and because worth is something you claim, not something stamped on you at decanting.
HOW   — By enhanced strength and reflexes, courier's tradecraft and cool nerve, the mentorship of "Boss," and at last the courage to stop hiding what she is and choose her own people and her own world.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was made, not born — and I am no less a person for it.

